<div class="page-container">
    <div class="top-section">
        <div class="search-section">
            <h1 class="header">Find that plate</h1>

            <div class="search-box">
                <%= form_with(url: '/search', method: "post") do %>
                <%= text_field_tag "home[number_plate]", nil, placeholder: "Enter the diplomatic number plate here e.g 20", autofocus: true %>
                <%= submit_tag("Search", class: "btn search-button") %>
                <% end %>
            </div>

            <div class="flash-messages">
                <% flash.each do |type, msg| %>
                <p class="alert alert-<%= type %> alert-dismissible">
                    <a href="#" class="close" data-dismiss="alert" aria-label="close">&times;</a>
                    <%= msg %>
                </p>
                <% end %>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="help-section">
        <div class="help-section-content">
            <h4 class="help-section-heading">About</h4>
            <p>
                Find That Plate is a search engine for number plates issued in Kenya. Currently, it supports diplomatic number plates.
                You can search using:
                <ul>
                    <li>a number such as 22</li>
                    <li>the full plate e.g 22 CD</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="help-section-content">
            <h4 class="help-section-heading">Origin story</h4>
            <p>Diplomatic plates are written with white on a red background. In Kenya, these number plates are issued based on the order that countries recognised Kenya as an independent state.</p>
            <p>The first country was Germany and their number plates start with 1 CD</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
